<section class="slide whiteSlide" data-name="p2" data-title="p2">
  <div class="content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="wrap padding-top-5">
        <div class="">
          <div class="left">
            <h3 class="font-weight-bold">Deeper Understanding</h3>
            <h1 class="huge fromLeft text-pink bold">HOW SYLLABI COULD SERVE</h1>
          </div>
          <ul class="grid">
            <li class="col-6-12 left cell-33">
              <div class="padding-right-5">
                <h2 class="small fromLeft bold text-teal">Who does your syllabus serve?</h2>
                <p class="fromLeft"><span class="opacity-8">Deconstructing your syllabus in terms of who it serves entails categorizing its
                 content by audiences. Pull out your syllabus anad follow along…</span></p>
                <ol class="list decimal margin-left-5 margin-top-2 margin-bottom-5">
                  <li class="margin-bottom-3">
                    <h3 class="medium h3">Write
                      <span class="text-teal">INSTITUTION</span>
                      next to sections required by your institution.
                    </h3>
                  </li>
                  <li class="margin-bottom-3">
                    <h3 class="medium h3">
                      Write
                      <span class="text-teal">DEPARTMENT</span>
                      next to the sections required by your department.
                    </h3>
                  </li>
                  <li class="margin-bottom-3">
                    <h3 class="medium h3">
                      Write <span class="text-teal">FACULTY</span> next to sections that explicate your
                       classroom rules/policies and the relationship you expect to have with students.
                     </h3>
                  </li>
                </ol>
                <div class="">
                  <p class="ae-1">As you deconstruct your syllabus, write down your observations — ideas, a-ha's, insights — and your sensemaking.</p>
                  <p class="ae-2"><span class="text-tea">Ask yourself:</span>
                    What is the process of deconstructing my syllabus helping me understand about who my syllabus serves?
                  </p>

                  <hr class="ae-3"/>

                  <ul class="flex">
                    <li class="col-8-12 left middle">
                      <h6 class="ae-4 text-teal">NEXT UP</h6>
                      <h3 class="ae-4 margin-top-1">
                        <%= link_to s5_4_path do %>
                          "Reflecting..."
                         <% end %>
                      </h3>
                    </li>
                    <li class="col-3-12 left right">
                      <img class="ae-4" width="605" src="<%= image_url("graphics/exercise-break.png") %>" alt="iPhones Thumbnail" data-action="zoom"/>
                    </li>
                  </ul>

                </div>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="col-6-12 right ae-4 fromRight">
              <img class="margin-top-5 margin-left-5"  data-action="zoom" width="1200" src="<%= image_url("graphics/syllabus.svg") %>"/>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="background" style="background-image:url(assets/img/background/img-33.jpg)"></div>
</section>
